📊Methodology – Bank Management System
🔹 1. Planning Phase
Identify project objectives and scope
Understand banking operations (accounts, transactions, loans)
Decide required modules and features
🔹 2. Requirement Analysis
Collect functional and non-functional requirements
Identify user roles (Admin, Staff, Customer)
Analyze system needs and constraints
🔹 3. System Design
Design system architecture (frontend, backend, database)
Create ER diagrams and Data Flow Diagrams (DFD)
Plan database tables (customers, accounts, transactions)
🔹 4. Implementation (Coding)
Develop modules using programming language (C++/Java/Python)
Create database and connect it with application
Implement features like login, deposit, withdrawal, transfer
🔹 5. Testing
Perform unit testing for each module
Check for errors and bugs
Ensure all functionalities work correctly
🔹 6. Deployment
Install the system on the required environment
Make it ready for users (bank staff/customers)
🔹 7. Maintenance
Fix bugs and errors after deployment
Update system features if needed
Improve performance and security


